{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Bug|type2=Grass}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Wormadam}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Bug|prevnum=412|prev=Burmy|nextnum=414|next=Mothim|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Wormadam\n|jname=ミノマダム\n|jtranslit=Minomadamu\n|tmname=Minomadam\n|forme=3\n|form1=Plant Cloak\n|form2=Sandy Cloak\n|form3=Trash Cloak\n|image=413Wormadam-Plant.png\n|image2=413Wormadam-Sandy.png\n|image3=413Wormadam-Trash.png\n|ndex=413\n|sdex=046\n|karea=Central\n|kdex=045\n|type1=Bug\n|type2=Grass\n|form2type1=Bug\n|form2type2=Ground\n|form3type1=Bug\n|form3type2=Steel\n|category=Bagworm\n|height-ftin=1\'08"\n|height-m=0.5\n|weight-lbs=14.3\n|weight-kg=6.5\n|abilitylayout=2\n|ability1=Anticipation\n|abilityd=Overcoat\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Bug\n|eggcycles=15\n|evforms=3\n|evtotal=2\n|evsd=2\n|evde2=2\n|evde3=1\n|evsd3=1\n|expyield=148\n|oldexp=159\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=254\n|color=Green\n|formcolors=yes\n|catchrate=45\n|body=05\n|pokefordex=wormadam\n|generation=4\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Wormadam\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ミノマダム\'\'\' \'\'Minomadam\'\') is a {{type|Bug}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation IV]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] from a [[gender|female]] {{p|Burmy}} starting at [[level]] 20. It is one of Burmy\'s final forms, the other being {{p|Mothim}}.\n\nIt has one of three different secondary types: {{t|Steel}}, {{t|Grass}}, or {{t|Ground}}, determined by its cloak. Its cloak is permanent and determined by the cloak that Burmy was in when it evolved.\n* In its \'\'\'Plant Cloak\'\'\', it is {{2t|Bug|Grass}}-type.\n* In its \'\'\'Sandy Cloak\'\'\', it is {{2t|Bug|Ground}}-type.\n* In its \'\'\'Trash Cloak\'\'\', it is {{2t|Bug|Steel}}-type.\n\n==Biology==\nWormadam is a black, bagworm-like Pokémon with a coat of leaves, sand, or building insulation that has fused with its body. It has oval eyes, a long pointed beak, and a long antenna with a coiled tip. The beak is tipped with varying colors depending on the coat. The coat forms a pair of arm-like structures near this Pokémon\'s head. The Plant Cloak form has several white flowers covering it, and gives Wormadam a green-tipped beak and large leaves for arms. It will be dotted with reddish-brown rocks, and have chains of pebbles for arms and a brown tipped beak if it has the Sandy Cloak. When covered by the Trash Cloak, it has a pink tipped beak and long, dark pink ribbons for arms. Wormadam that evolve on cold days are said to form thicker cloaks. It is a female-only species, with {{p|Mothim}} as its male counterpart.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Cheryl Wormadam Plant Cloak.png|thumb|left|220px|Plant Cloak Wormadam in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n\n===Major appearances===\nAll three forms of Wormadam debuted in \'\'[[DP030|Some Enchanted Sweetening!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Cheryl]]. She sent them out to show {{Ash}}, {{an|Dawn}}, and {{an|Brock}} that she had not been successful in finding a male Burmy to evolve into a Mothim. She then had her Wormadam cheer for Burmy while he battled to gain experience.\n\nA Sandy Cloak Wormadam appeared in \'\'[[DP114|Another One Gabites the Dust!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Ursula]]. She used her in the [[Appeal|Performance Stage]] of the {{to|Chocovine}} {{pkmn|Contest}}, allowing Ursula to move on to the [[Contest Battle]]s.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA group of Plant Cloak Wormadam appeared in \'\'[[M10|The Rise of Darkrai]]\'\'.\n\nA Plant Cloak Wormadam appeared in \'\'[[XY001|Kalos, Where Dreams and Adventures Begin!]]\'\'.\n\nA Plant Cloak Wormadam briefly appeared in \'\'[[XY049|Bonnie for the Defense!]]\'\'.\n\nAll three forms of Wormadam appeared in \'\'[[M19|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel]]\'\' as residents of the [[Nebel Plateau]].\n\n<gallery>\nCheryl Wormadam Sandy Cloak.png|Sandy Cloak Wormadam in the anime\nCheryl Wormadam Trash Cloak.png|Trash Cloak Wormadam in the anime\n</gallery>\n{{-}}\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP030|Wormadam|Ash\'s Pokédex|Wormadam, the Bagworm Pokémon, and the evolved form of a female {{p|Burmy}}. Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Meragura Volcano various Pokémon.png|thumb|Plant Cloak Wormadam in [[Pokémon Try Adventure]]]]\n===In the [[Pokémon Adventures]] manga===\nWormadam was first seen in a Sandy Cloak in \'\'[[PS384|Maddening Magby]]\'\', under the ownership of one of the members of the [[Celestic Town]] brigade that Cynthia assembled.\n\nIn \'\'[[PS426|Softening Up Kakuna]]\'\', a Trash Cloak Wormadam was used by a {{tc|Youngster}} that was challenging the {{gdis|Battle Factory|IV}}.\n\nIn \'\'[[PS435|The Final Dimensional Duel V]]\'\', a Plant Cloak Wormadam appeared on [[Fullmoon Island]] in {{FB|Tower Tycoon|Palmer}}\'s flashback.\n\n===In [[Pokémon Try Adventure]] manga===\nSeveral Plant Cloak Wormadam were seen around [[Meragura Volcano]].\n{{-}}\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Wormadam (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Bug|type2=Grass}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=IV}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=IV|reg1=Sinnoh|num1=046|reg2=Johto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Diamond|entry=When Burmy [[Evolution|evolved]], its cloak became a part of this Pokémon\'s body. The cloak is never shed.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Pearl|entry=Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Platinum|entry=When evolving, its body takes in surrounding materials. As a result, there are many body variations.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=HeartGold|v2=SoulSilver|entry=It is said that a Wormadam that evolves on a cold day will have a thicker cloak.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=V|reg1=Unova}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black|v2=White|t=FFF|entry=When evolving, its body takes in surrounding materials. As a result, there are ma